
1. Explain the core difference between Power BI and Looker.

	Power BI is a visual-first drag-and-drop tool with built-in data modeling (DAX/Power Query). Looker is a code-first platform using LookML (SQL-based modeling language) for centralized data definitions.​

| Power BI                  | Looker                  |
| ------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| Visual reports/dashboards | Semantic data layer     |
| DAX formulas              | LookML (Git-controlled) |
| Microsoft ecosystem       | Google Cloud native     |
| Point-and-click           | Developer-focused       |



2. Which tool is best for cloud-based analytics and why?

Looker wins for cloud analytics:

    Native Google Cloud BigQuery integration

    Real-time SQL querying (no data import)

    Serverless scaling for massive datasets

    Embedded analytics in web apps

Power BI imports data first, creating delays for live cloud data.



3. Why is Power BI considered beginner-friendly?

Power BI's "no-code" approach:

1. Drag data → Auto-creates visuals
2. Natural language Q&A ("sales last month")
3. 1000+ pre-built templates
4. Excel-like interface
5. AI visuals (key influencers, decomposition tree)

Looker requires SQL + LookML knowledge = steep learning curve



4. How does Looker use SQL for reporting?

Looker = SQL + LookML:

1. Write LookML models (metrics, dimensions)
2. Git version control
3. Generates SQL automatically
4. Users explore via drag-drop interface
5. Changes to model → All reports update

Example LookML:

measure: total_sales {
  type: sum
  sql: ${sale_amount} ;;
}

Benefit: Single source of truth - change metric definition once, everywhere updates.



5. When should a company choose Looker over Power BI?

| Scenario              | Why Looker          |
| --------------------- | ------------------- |
| Data team exists      | LookML expertise    |
| Google Cloud user     | BigQuery native     |
| Enterprise governance | Centralized metrics |
| Embedded analytics    | Websites/apps       |
| Developer culture     | Git workflows       |


Choose Power BI when:

    Small/medium business

    Microsoft 365 users

